III. THE COUPLED SYSTEM
This Section derives the equations that govern the dynamics of a fluid membrane embedded in a surrounding fluid driven by curvature elasticity and line tension. Line tension arises when the membrane is not closed or has several phases. We present each phenomenon separately, and couple all together through the principle of virtual power.
